text: yesterday was my 27th birthday or my
first day entering the late 20s time
flies by so fast I still feel like I'm
18 and I think I'll always feel that way
at heart for the better part of the last
six years since I studied abroad in
Prague I've been living and traveling
overseas I've been to 139 countries and
I have my eyes set on the last 54 to
complete the world Travel has changed me
in more ways than I ever imagined it has
provided me with a valuable education
learning languages immersing into
cultures and discovering lifestyles has
taught me more than I ever learned in
school travel has showed me that the
world is a safer place and I thought it
showed me that every human has the same
wants and needs to love and be loved
to make money to survive to have food
and shelter and to maintain close
relationship with their family and
friends Travel has taught me to be
simple I used to own a room full of
things a hundred pounds and now all of
my possessions fit into these two
backpacks Travel has led me to meeting
my soul mate my travel companion who has
changed my life for the better where are
we yeah I get more satisfaction from
seeing the world through her eyes than I
do through mine visiting 139 countries
has made me realize how little I've
actually seen in the world even the
smallest countries have so much to offer
hey guys I'm here at terminus day this
stunning country which honestly is super
underrated trying to communicate with
someone who I have nothing in common
with language race religion belief has
become routine for me so we're here in
the Mersey tribe and omo valley ethiopia
and to be honest i am more in my element
with those people than i am surrounded
by Americans discovering impoverished
areas has taught me to appreciate the
things I have it has proven to me that
happiness is in no way dependent on
money some of the happiest people I've
ever seen we're living in the poorest
areas I've ever been stepping out of my
comfort zone has led me to be a more
confident person I was scared of heights
until I went bungee jumping in
Switzerland scared of spiders until I
ate one in Cambodia and frightened of
sharks until I dived with them in Fiji
within five years of graduating college
I have turned a passion for travelling
into a career it's now impossible for me
to go back home to live the American
dream at a corporate office with a boss
telling me what to do even if I made a
seven-figure
income I still wouldn't do it because
travel has taught me to rise above money
travel has made me realize that close
relationships with family friends and a
significant other is all you need to be
happy not a big house or a fancy car so
at this time as I turned 27 years old
all I want to do is travel I'm drew
pinsky and if you like my travel videos
please click Subscribe and join me as I
plan to visit every country in the world
